<p>Redshift from gravity. Fire a photon up. Convert into mass and let mass drop. If energy conserved then you gain mgh of energy where $ m = \hbar \omegaâ€™$, the freqeuncy at the top. Hence you have $ \hbar \omega = m+mgh=\hbar \omega (1+gh)$.</p>

